  "chapter": {
    "number": 3,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Prophet’s Afflictions"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3357
          },
          {
            "text": "am the man who has seen affliction",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "under the rod of God’s wrath.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has driven me away and made me walk",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in darkness instead of light.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Indeed, He keeps turning His hand",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "against me all day long.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has worn away my flesh and skin;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has shattered my bones.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has besieged me and surrounded me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with bitterness and hardship.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has made me dwell in darkness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like those dead for ages.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has walled me in so I cannot escape;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has weighed me down with chains.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Even when I cry out and plead for help,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He shuts out my prayer.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has barred my ways with cut stones;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has made my paths crooked.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He is a bear lying in wait,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a lion hiding in ambush.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He forced me off my path and tore me to pieces;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He left me without help.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He bent His bow",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and set me as the target for His arrow.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He pierced my kidneys",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with His arrows.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I am a laughingstock to all my people;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they mock me in song all day long.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has filled me with bitterness;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has intoxicated me with wormwood.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has ground my teeth with gravel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and trampled me in the dust.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My soul has been deprived of peace;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have forgotten what prosperity is.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So I say, “My strength has perished,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "along with my hope from the LORD.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Prophet’s Hope"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Remember my affliction and wandering,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the wormwood and the gall.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely my soul remembers",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and is humbled within me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet I call this to mind,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and therefore I have hope:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Because of the loving devotion",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3358
          },
          {
            "text": "of the LORD we are not consumed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for His mercies never fail.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They are new every morning;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "great is Your faithfulness!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“The LORD is my portion,” says my soul,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“therefore I will hope in Him.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD is good to those who wait for Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the soul who seeks Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It is good to wait quietly",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the salvation of the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It is good for a man to bear the yoke",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "while he is still young.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let him sit alone in silence,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for God has disciplined him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let him bury his face in the dust—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "perhaps there is still hope.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let him offer his cheek to the one who would strike him;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let him be filled with reproach.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the Lord will not",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "cast us off forever.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Even if He causes grief, He will show compassion",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "according to His abundant loving devotion.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 33,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For He does not willingly afflict",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or grieve the sons of men.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 34,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "To crush underfoot",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all the prisoners of the land,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 35,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "to deny a man justice",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "before the Most High,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 36,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "to subvert a man in his lawsuit—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "of these the Lord does not approve.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Justice"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 37,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who has spoken and it came to pass,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "unless the Lord has ordained it?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 38,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not both adversity and good",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "come from the mouth of the Most High?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 39,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why should any mortal man complain,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in view of his sins?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 40,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let us examine and test our ways,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and turn back to the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 41,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let us lift up our hearts and hands",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to God in heaven:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 42,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“We have sinned and rebelled;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You have not forgiven.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 43,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have covered Yourself in anger and pursued us;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You have killed without pity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 44,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have covered Yourself with a cloud",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that no prayer can pass through.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 45,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have made us scum and refuse",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "among the nations.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 46,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All our enemies",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "open their mouths against us.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 47,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Panic and pitfall have come upon us—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "devastation and destruction.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 48,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Streams of tears flow from my eyes",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "over the destruction of the daughter of my people.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 49,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My eyes overflow unceasingly,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "without relief,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 50,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "until the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "looks down from heaven and sees.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 51,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My eyes bring grief to my soul",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because of all the daughters of my city.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 52,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Without cause my enemies",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "hunted me like a bird.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 53,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They dropped me alive into a pit",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and cast stones upon me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 54,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The waters flowed over my head,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I thought I was going to die.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 55,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I called on Your name, O LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "out of the depths of the Pit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 56,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You heard my plea:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Do not ignore my cry for relief.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 57,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You drew near when I called on You;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You said, “Do not be afraid.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 58,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You defend my cause, O Lord;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You redeem my life.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 59,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have seen, O LORD, the wrong done to me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "vindicate my cause!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 60,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have seen all their malice,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all their plots against me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 61,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O LORD, You have heard their insults,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all their plots against me—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 62,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "the slander and murmuring of my assailants",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "against me all day long.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 63,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When they sit and when they rise,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "see how they mock me in song.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 64,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will pay them back what they deserve, O LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "according to the work of their hands.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 65,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Put a veil of anguish over their hearts;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "may Your curse be upon them!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 66,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will pursue them in anger and exterminate them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from under Your heavens, O LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 3357,
